==Constellations depicted==
The constellations depicted, in the order they are listed on the cards, are:<ref name=Ridpath /> [[Draco (constellation)|Draco]], [[Ursa Minor]], [[Camelopardalis]], [[Tarandus (constellation)|Tarandus]] (a now-obsolete constellation representing a reindeer, also called Rangifer),<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ianridpath.com/startales/rangifer.htm |title=Rangifer|last=[[Ian Ridpath|Ridpath, Ian]]|work=Star Tales|accessdate=7 March 2014}}</ref> [[Custos Messium]] (another obsolete constellation, literally translated as the Harvest Keeper, but intended as a pun on the comet hunter [[Charles Messier]].)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ianridpath.com/startales/custosmessium.htm |title=Custos Messium|last=[[Ian Ridpath|Ridpath, Ian]]|work=Star Tales|accessdate=7 March 2014}}</ref>, [[Cassiopeia (constellation)|Cassiopeia]], [[Cepheus (constellation)|Cepheus]], [[Gloria Frederici]] (another obsolete constellation, also called Honores Friderici, meant to commemorate Frederick the Great)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ianridpath.com/startales/honoresfriderici.htm|title=Honores Friderici|last=[[Ian Ridpath|Ridpath, Ian]]|work=Star Tales|accessdate=7 March 2014}}</ref>, [[Andromeda (constellation)|Andromeda]], [[Triangulum|Triangula]], [[Perseus (constellation)|Perseus]], [[Auriga (constellation)|Auriga]], [[Lynx (constellation)]], [[Telescopium Herschilii]] (another obsolete constellation, the Telescope of [[William Herschel]]),<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ianridpath.com/startales/telher.htm|title=Telescopium Herschilii|last=[[Ian Ridpath|Ridpath, Ian]]|work=Star Tales|accessdate=7 March 2014}}</ref> [[Ursa Major]], [[Bo<U+00F6>tes (constellation)|Bo<U+00F6>tes]], [[Canes Venatici]], [[Coma Berenices]], [[Quadrans Muralis]] (obsolete again: a constellation created by [[Joseph J<U+00E9>r<U+00F4>me de Lalande|Lalande]] to commemorate the wall-mounted [[quadrant (instrument)|quadrant]] he and his nephew used to measure star positions),<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.ianridpath.com/startales/quadrans.htm |title=Quadrans Muralis|last=[[Ian Ridpath|Ridpath, Ian]]|work=Star Tales|accessdate=7 March 2014}}</ref> [[Hercules (constellation)]], [[Corona Borealis]], [[Taurus Poniatowski]] (obsolete again: A constellation representing the bull on King [[Stanis<U+0142>aw August Poniatowski]]'s coat of arms. Also called [[Taurus Poniatovii]].),<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ianridpath.com/startales/poniatowski.htm|title=Taurus Poniatovii|last=[[Ian Ridpath|Ridpath, Ian]]|work=Star Tales|accessdate=7 March 2014}}</ref> [[Serpentarius]] (a former name for [[Ophiuchus]])<ref name=Ridpath />, [[Scutum Sobiesky]] (Full name of the constellation [[Scutum]], the Shield of King [[John III Sobieski]].)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ianridpath.com/startales/scutum.htm|title=Scutum|last=[[Ian Ridpath|Ridpath, Ian]]|work=Star Tales|accessdate=7 March 2014}}</ref> [[Serpens]], [[Delphinus]], [[Sagitta]], [[Aquila (constellation)|Aquila]], [[Antinous (constellation)]] (another obsolete constellation, [[Antinous]] was the lover of the roman emperor [[Hadrian]].)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ianridpath.com/startales/antinous.htm|title=Antinous|last=[[Ian Ridpath|Ridpath, Ian]]|work=Star Tales|accessdate=7 March 2014}}</ref> [[Lacerta]], [[Cygnus (constellation)|Cygnus]], [[Lyra]], [[Vulpecula and Anser]] (a slightly Anglicised version of the full name of [[Vulpecula]]. It translates as "The little fox and the goose".)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ianridpath.com/startales/vulpecula.htm|title=Vulpecula|last=[[Ian Ridpath|Ridpath, Ian]]|work=Star Tales|accessdate=7 March 2014}}</ref> [[Pegasus (constellation)|Pegasus]], [[Equuleus]], [[Aries (constellation)|Aries]], [[Musca Borealis]] (another obsolete constellation: a fly, not to be confused with the modern southern constellation of [[Musca (constellation)|Musca]].)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ianridpath.com/startales/muscaborealis.htm|title=Musca Borealis|last=[[Ian Ridpath|Ridpath, Ian]]|work=Star Tales|accessdate=7 March 2014}}</ref> [[Taurus (constellation)|Taurus]], [[Gemini (constellation)|Gemini]], [[Cancer (constellation)]], [[Leo Major]] (a.k.a. [[Leo (constellation)|Leo]]), [[Leo Minor]], [[Virgo (constellation)|Virgo]], [[Libra (constellation)|Libra]], [[Scorpio (constellation)|Scorpio]], [[Sagittarius (constellation)|Sagittarius]], [[Corona Australis (constellation)|Corona Australis]], [[Microscopium]], [[Telescopium]], [[Capricornus]], [[Aquarius (constellation)|Aquarius]], [[Piscis Australis]] (a.k.a. [[Piscis Austrinus]]), [[Ballon Aerostatique]] (An obsolete constellation meant to honour the [[Montgolfier brothers]]' balloon, also called [[Globus Aerostaticus]]),<ref>{{cite web|url=http://http://www.ianridpath.com/startales/globusaerostaticus.htm|title=Globus Aerostaticus|last=[[Ian Ridpath|Ridpath, Ian]]|work=Star Tales|accessdate=7 March 2014}}</ref> [[Pisces (constellation)|Pisces]], [[Psalterium Georgii]] (also obsolete, the harp of King [[George III of England]].),<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ianridpath.com/startales/harpa.htm|title=Harpa Georgii|last=[[Ian Ridpath|Ridpath, Ian]]|work=Star Tales|accessdate=7 March 2014}}</ref> [[Fluvius Eridanus]] (More commonly simply named Eridanus),<ref>{{cite book |last=Hill |first=John |date=1754 |title= |url=http://books.google.co.uk/books?id=lzigAAAAMAAJ&dq=john+hill+urania&pg=PT304&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q=fluvius&f=false |location=London |publisher=T. Gardner|accessdate=7 March 2014 |chapter=Fluvius| page= [unpaginated]}}</ref> [[Cetus (constellation)|Cetus]], [[Officina Sculptoris]] (a.k.a. [[Sculptor (constellation)|Sculptor]]), [[Fornax Chemica]] (a.k.a. [[Fornax]]), [[Machina Electrica]] (obsolete, represented an electrostatic generator),<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ianridpath.com/startales/machina.htm|title=Machina Electrica|last=[[Ian Ridpath|Ridpath, Ian]]|work=Star Tales|accessdate=7 March 2014}}</ref>  [[Orion (constellation)|Orion]], [[Canis Major]], [[Lepus (constellation)|Lepus]] [[Columba Noachi]] (a.k.a [[Columba (constellation)|Columba]]),<ref>{{cite book |last=Hill |first=John |date=1754 |title= |url=http://books.google.co.uk/books?id=lzigAAAAMAAJ&dq=john+hill+urania&pg=PT304&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q=fluvius&f=false |location=London |publisher=T. Gardner|accessdate=7 March 2014 |chapter=Pigeon| page= [unpaginated]}}</ref> Cela Sculptoris (a.k.a. [[Caelum (constellation)|Caelum]]),<ref name=Ridpath /> [[Monoceros (constellation)|Monoceros]], [[Canis Minor (constellation)|Canis Minor]], [[Atelier Typographique]] (obsolete, represented [[Johannes Gutenberg|Gutenberg]]'s printing shop),<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ianridpath.com/startales/officina.htm|title=Officina Typographica|last=[[Ian Ridpath|Ridpath, Ian]]|work=Star Tales|accessdate=7 March 2014}}</ref> [[Noctua (constellation)|Noctua]] (obsolete, an owl replacing the equally obsolete [[Turdus Solitarius]]),<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ianridpath.com/startales/solitaire.htm|title=Turdus Solitarius|last=[[Ian Ridpath|Ridpath, Ian]]|work=Star Tales|accessdate=7 March 2014}}</ref> [[Corvus (constellation)|Corvus]], [[Crater (constellation)|Crater]], [[Sextans Uraniae]] (original name of [[Sextans]]),<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ianridpath.com/startales/sextans.htm|title=Sextans|last=[[Ian Ridpath|Ridpath, Ian]]|work=Star Tales|accessdate=7 March 2014}}</ref> [[Hydra (constellation)|Hydra]], [[Felis (constellation)]] (obsolete, represented a cat)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ianridpath.com/startales/felis.htm|title=Felis|last=[[Ian Ridpath|Ridpath, Ian]]|work=Star Tales|accessdate=7 March 2014}}</ref> [[Lupus (constellation)|Lupus]], [[Centaurus]], [[Antlia Pneumatica]] (a.k.a. [[Antlia]]),<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ianridpath.com/startales/antlia.htm|title=Antlia|last=[[Ian Ridpath|Ridpath, Ian]]|work=Star Tales|accessdate=7 March 2014}}</ref> [[Argo Navis]] (obsolete, as is now divided into [[Carina (constellation)|Carina]], [[Vela (constellation)|Vela]], and [[Puppis]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ianridpath.com/startales/argo.htm|title=Argo Navis|last=[[Ian Ridpath|Ridpath, Ian]]|work=Star Tales|accessdate=7 March 2014}}</ref> and [[Pyxis Nautica]] (a.k.a. [[Pyxis]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ianridpath.com/startales/pyxis.htm|title=Pyxis|last=[[Ian Ridpath|Ridpath, Ian]]|work=Star Tales|accessdate=7 March 2014}}</ref>

In addition, [[Mons M<U+00E6>nalus]] is shown below [[Bo<U+00F6>tes (constellation)|Bo<U+00F6>tes]], Caput Medus<U+00E6> is shown as part of Perseus, and [[Cerberus (constellation)|Cerberus]] is shown with [[Hercules (constellation)|Hercules]]<ref name=Ridpath />

